metadata.name: Fontana - MARCEL DUCHAMP (FALSE!)
metadata.description:
Fontana is a ready-made work made by artist Marcel Duchamp in 1917. It was never exposed to the public and was later lost.

It consists of a common urinal signed "R. Mutt" is titled Fontana, and is considered by some art historians and specialized theorists to be one of the greatest works of art of the twentieth century. Since 1964 there have been sixteen replicas of the object in the world.

NOT TODAY!

The most sceptical say that these works are false, experts say they are imitations. WHAT DO YOU SAY?
